      "comment_id" : 128537158,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "I think Spring guarantees that singletons are created only once. If anyone claims this isn&#39;t the case then I would ask for more concrete evidence. I think the below answer is correct : <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/3406690/157591\">stackoverflow.com/a/3406690/157591</a> @PostConstruct was designed to work with setter injection. If you use constructor injection then it isn&#39;t needed"
